$interpreted: Karnulla: Tsk, thanks to that stupid mermaid, the planned feast is now all down the drain...
Little Frogodile: Gegaga, gagagaga!
Karnulla: What, humans trespassing into our territory?
Little Frogodile: Gaga!
Karnulla: Well, unfortunate for him. I'm in a really terrible mood right now. Take me to him. I will make him regret ever stepping foot in here!
Skinny Hunter: ...Yikes. this place is so stuffy. Nothing but mud puddles on the paths too. At this pace, my feet are gonna rot from soaking in all this muddy water!
Simon: Quit whining. If not for the screw up with the underground factory and that fatty Lucky kicking the bucket for no apparent reason,
Simon: you and I wouldn't have to change jobs either. Need to feed ourselves after all.
Poor Hunter: Boss Simon, are you sure this will really work out?
Simon: The shores of Maple Lake are filled with all kinds of obscure creatures.
Simon: As long as we capture the ones that sell for the big bucks, the income will definitely be better than building a factory and selling drugs.
Simon: A frogodile!? Their skin can be made into high-priced leather goods. Those often get really good prices in the Desert Bazaar!
Karnulla: You bastards, get off our territory, now!
Skinny Hunter: It can even talk!?
Simon: Looks like it's a rare species...good, the big one must be captured alive. Everyone, go get them!
Karnulla: Damnit, let go of my boys!
Simon: No need to be concerned about them, 'cuz you're joining them very soon!
Dark Colored Frogodile: Gagaga!!
Simon: Bug off! Stop getting in my way!
Karnulla: It's you!? I just called you idiot back then...
Dark Colored Frogodile: GA! Gaga!!
Karnulla: ......
Karnulla: Got it. Boys, hold on. I will definitely come back to rescue you!
Simon: Darn it, the biggest prize got away...
Skinny Hunter: Boss Simon, what do we do now?
Simon: Release the wolves we raised to track it down. We shall continue to search for other valuable prey.
Skinny Hunter: Understood!
